<co-content>
 <p variant="body1">
  In accordance with
  <a href="https://www.colorado.edu/sccr/students/honor-code-and-student-code-conduct" title="">
   <u>
    CU Boulder’s Honor Code
   </u>
  </a>
  and
  <a href="https://www.coursera.support/s/article/learner-000001214?language=en_US" title="">
   <u>
    Coursera’s Honor Code
   </u>
  </a>
  , AI use is permitted in MS-CS coursework unless otherwise specified, but this use must be properly cited and acknowledged.
 </p>
 <p variant="body1">
  For both written and coding assignments, any outputs from AI that are incorporated, including direct quotation, paraphrasing, and rephrasing, should be cited appropriately. A citation should also be given for outputs from the AI resulting from editing, grammar correction, or translation. For written assignments, use the citation style specified or used in the course, and if this is not given, please use APA. For code, put a comment above the code with the corresponding citation and the lines it applies to. Please refer to
  <a href="https://libguides.brown.edu/c.php?g=1338928&amp;p=9868287" title="">
   <u>
    Brown University’s guide to Citation and Attribution for AI tools
   </u>
  </a>
  for more details.
 </p>
 <p variant="body1">
  Any AI use should always be acknowledged, whether or not its output was directly used in your work in a way that requires citation. Along with the written or coding assignment, you should provide an acknowledgement section that details the following: the AI tools you used and for what purpose, the prompts used, and how you have adapted, changed, or added to the AI output at each iteration. For more details and examples of acknowledgement sections, refer to
  <a href="https://www.monash.edu/student-academic-success/build-digital-capabilities/create-online/acknowledging-the-use-of-generative-artificial-intelligence#tabs__3254796-01" title="">
   <u>
    Monash University’s guide on Acknowledging the use of generative artificial intelligence
   </u>
  </a>
  .
 </p>
 <p variant="body1">
  As always, be sure to review the specific course and assignment details for what AI use is acceptable and what is prohibited. Additionally, if asked, you should be prepared to present documentation of your AI use that supports and aligns with the acknowledgement statement you provided.
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
</co-content>
