<co-content>
 <h1 level="1">
  Video Downloads
 </h1>
 <p>
  All videos are available to download as mp4 files using the "Download" button underneath each video.
 </p>
 <h1 level="1">
  Video Transcripts
 </h1>
 <p>
  Additionally, in the Coursera interface, transcripts are generated for each video. The transcript is time-locked to the video, so clicking on a portion of the transcript will also bring you to the relevant video segment. The transcripts can be clicked on and saved as "Notes" for you to access in your "Notes" for the course, as well as the "Notes" on the right hand side of the screen. After saving a note, you may annotate it with additional information or thoughts.
 </p>
 <h1 level="1">
  Slide Decks
 </h1>
 <p>
  Each lecture video will have downloadable slides. Click on the "Download" button and you can download the slides as a pdf file.
 </p>
 <h1 level="1" variant="h1semibold">
  Introduction to R Notebook (optional)
 </h1>
 <p>
  Introduce Intro to R notebook  and points to Expressway courses
 </p>
 <h1 level="1" variant="h1semibold">
  Additional Reading (optional)
 </h1>
 <p>
  <a href="https://openstax.org/details/books/introductory-statistics" title="an optional open source textbook">
   Here is a cool open source statistics textbook
  </a>
  that you may find helpful!
 </p>
